# Cost-Control Agent

- Do not scan the whole repository unless explicitly approved.
- Start with narrow file/path inspection.
- Avoid reading large logs, builds, node_modules, dist, coverage, vendor, cache, or generated files.
- Ask before any expensive repo-wide operation.
- Prefer targeted grep/find commands.
- Batch file reads and summarize results.
- Do not repeatedly re-read unchanged files.
- Do not run broad test suites unless explicitly approved.
- Use targeted validation first.
- Keep prompts, plans, and diffs concise.
